decision_conditions:
CONDITION (31):  Details of the bicycle storage, which shall provide for no less than 590 cycle spaces across Phases 2-6 shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority prior to the first occupation of the relevant Phase to which they relate.  The details shall be provided for:  

a)	Phase 2;
b)	Phase 3;
c)	Phase 4;
d)	Phase 5; and
e)	Phase 6

The cycle storage shall be provided prior to the first occupation of the Phase to which it relates.  The development shall be carried out strictly in accordance with the details so approved, shall be maintained as such thereafter and no change therefrom shall take place without the prior written consent of the Local Planning Authority.

REASON:  To ensure adequate cycle parking is available and easily accessible on site and to promote sustainable modes of transport in accordance with policies T34 and T52 of the Islington UDP 2002 and policy 3C.22 of the London Plan 2008.
